.TH "prm_was_any_context_lost_old" 9 "prm_was_any_context_lost_old" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
prm_was_any_context_lost_old \- was device context lost? (old API)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" prm_was_any_context_lost_old
.BI "(u8 part "  ","
.BI "s16 inst "  ","
.BI "u16 idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "part" 12
PRM partition ID (e.g., OMAP4430_PRM_PARTITION)
.IP "inst" 12
PRM instance offset (e.g., OMAP4430_PRM_MPU_INST)
.IP "idx" 12
CONTEXT register offset
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 1 if any bits were set in the *_CONTEXT_* register
identified by (\fIpart\fP, \fIinst\fP, \fIidx\fP), which means that some context
was lost for that module; otherwise, return 0.  XXX Deprecated;
callers need to use a less-SoC-dependent way to identify hardware
IP blocks.
